other_tests.findings: Fluid-filled tubular structure in the right lower quadrant in the region of the appendix with hyperenhancement of the mucosal wall measuring up to 7 mm with surrounding inflammatory changes in the fat. No evidence of distinct periappendiceal fluid collections. No free air noted throughout the abdomen. The visualized portions of the stomach and loops of small and large bowel are normal. The spleen, kidneys, liver, gallbladder, and pancreas are normal.
